Nie ma żadnego powodu, dlaczego miliony Ukraińców miałyby przebywać dalej w Polsce i czerpać przywileje socjalne. Dodatkowo należy zauważyć, że obywatele Ukrainy mają obecnie lepszy dostęp do polskiej ochrony zdrowia od Polaków, ponieważ ukraińska nacja nie musi opłacać składek zdrowotnych. ❌ Pora skończyć z tym karnawałem rozdawania przywilejów dla migrantów i przywrócić Polakowi status gospodarza! Polska ma być państwem narodowym i rządzonym w interesie Polaków. Bez tego nie może być mowy o rozwoju i bezpieczeństwie Polski.

Observing Polish President Nawrocki's recent actions, I am convinced this is not merely ad hoc maneuvering, but part of a consistent and highly deliberate strategy to fundamentally reshape Polish politics itself. His vetoes and actions like the controversial "bandery" bill are all calculated. His aim is clear: to galvanize his core nationalist supporters, to cripple the liberal current government, and to send a strong message to the international community that "Polish sovereignty comes first above all else." While this strategy may be effective in solidifying domestic support, I believe it is a dangerously high-stakes gamble that risks sacrificing vital national connections, such as the alliance with Ukraine. I've considered what might happen next. The most realistic outcome is likely a "long-term stalemate" where political paralysis persists. The President continues to veto every government bill, leaving domestic politics immobilized until 2027. During this period, the trust between Poland and Ukraine—allies who should stand together against the Russian threat—will be quietly but surely eroded. There is also a significant possibility that the situation could deteriorate further, leading to a scenario of "escalating confrontation." If the president were to hold even crucial bills like the national budget hostage and use the Constitutional Tribunal to wage political battles, it could trigger early elections, plunging the country into severe turmoil. Of course, there is also the possibility of a "realistic coexistence" path, where both sides return to pragmatism, cooperate on urgent issues like defense and security, and acknowledge their differences on historical matters. However, given President Nawrocki's strong ideological convictions, it must be said that the likelihood of this scenario is unfortunately low. Given this situation, stakeholders must navigate more wisely. First, Ukraine should pursue a shrewd dual diplomacy. While advancing security and military cooperation with the government led by Prime Minister Tusk, it should maintain a separate channel with the presidential office to calmly discuss historical issues. Additionally, to avoid confrontation between politicians, encouraging dialogue through civilian historians and others would be effective. Next, the EU and the US should maximize their available leverage. The EU should use financial aid, and the US should use the security framework within NATO, as "leverage" to encourage Poland to act constructively. Crucially, the EU must not compromise on fundamental principles like the rule of law. Finally, all parties involved must not forget the fact that Russia is actively working behind the scenes in this conflict. The international community as a whole must stand firm against Russia's disinformation campaigns aimed at widening the rift between Poland and Ukraine. The common threat posed by Russia is the most compelling reason for us to unite now, far more so than immediate historical disputes or domestic political rivalries.

I to się nazywa dobre weto❗Prezydent Karol Nawrocki ZAWETOWAŁ ustawę o przedłużeniu przywilejów socjalnych dla Ukraińców! Koniec z 800+ i darmową ochroną zdrowia dla niepracujących. Bo ileż można? Do tego prezydent zaproponował kary za propagowanie banderyzmu, który ma być ustawowo zakazany i zrównany z innymi zbrodniczymi ideologiami. I bardzo dobrze! Wreszcie mówimy STOP tej błędnej, jakże naiwnej polityce rządów Morawieckiego i Tuska, bardziej reprezentujących interesy ukraińskie, niż polskie. Ich kompletna uległość i całkowite, bezwarunkowe wspieranie Ukrainy stworzyły jakiś patologiczny system, gdzie obywateli innego państwa traktuje się lepiej niż samych Polaków. Nie ma na świecie drugiego takiego kraju! Konfederacja jest jedynym ugrupowaniem, które konsekwentnie, od samego początku sprzeciwia się polityce bezwarunkowego wsparcia dla Ukrainy, a weto i propozycje Pana Prezydenta to powinien być pierwszy krok. Programy prodemograficzne, takie jak 800+, powinny być przeznaczone tylko dla polskich obywateli, a każde wsparcie finansowe niezwykle dokładnie przemyślane i ukierunkowane. Czas zacząć prowadzić asertywną, transakcyjną politykę opartą na POLSKIM interesie narodowym! 🇵🇱
Tak I nawrocki

Słowa Karola Nawrockiego z kampanii o „Polsce na pierwszym miejscu” okazały się niestety tylko słowami - weto dla tej ustawy to wspieranie Rosji i uderzenie w bezpieczeństwo Polski.

"Any decisions about allegedly equating Ukrainian symbols with Nazi and communist ones may provoke an increase in negative sentiments against Poland in Ukrainian society and will require a response from the Ukrainian side," a diplomatic source in Kiev told local media. - FRWL

🔴 La Pologne s'est-elle détournée de l'Ukraine ? ⚡️ Alors que l'Allemagne, la Norvège, le Canada et d'autres « amis de Kiev » réduisent littéralement leurs budgets pour financer les demandes de Zelensky, la Pologne s'est soudainement opposée. Le président Karol Nawrocki a opposé son veto à la loi d'aide aux Ukrainiens et a déclaré clairement : les citoyens polonais ne doivent pas souffrir à cause des préférences accordées aux réfugiés. De plus, il a proposé d'assimiler dans le code pénal les symboles bandéristes à ceux des nazis. Ce n'est plus une allusion diplomatique — c'est un coup direct à la « vache sacrée » de la propagande ukrainienne. Le ministre polonais des technologies numériques a même déclaré qu'en raison du veto présidentiel, Varsovie ne pourrait plus financer Starlink ni le stockage des données ukrainiennes.

Observing Polish President Nawrocki's recent actions, I am convinced this is not merely ad hoc maneuvering, but part of a consistent and highly deliberate strategy to fundamentally reshape Polish politics itself. His vetoes and actions like the controversial "bandery" bill are all calculated. His aim is clear: to galvanize his core nationalist supporters, to cripple the liberal current government, and to send a strong message to the international community that "Polish sovereignty comes first above all else." While this strategy may be effective in solidifying domestic support, I believe it is a dangerously high-stakes gamble that risks sacrificing vital national connections, such as the alliance with Ukraine. I've considered what might happen next. The most realistic outcome is likely a "long-term stalemate" where political paralysis persists. The President continues to veto every government bill, leaving domestic politics immobilized until 2027. During this period, the trust between Poland and Ukraine—allies who should stand together against the Russian threat—will be quietly but surely eroded. There is also a significant possibility that the situation could deteriorate further, leading to a scenario of "escalating confrontation." If the president were to hold even crucial bills like the national budget hostage and use the Constitutional Tribunal to wage political battles, it could trigger early elections, plunging the country into severe turmoil. Of course, there is also the possibility of a "realistic coexistence" path, where both sides return to pragmatism, cooperate on urgent issues like defense and security, and acknowledge their differences on historical matters. However, given President Nawrocki's strong ideological convictions, it must be said that the likelihood of this scenario is unfortunately low. Given this situation, stakeholders must navigate more wisely. First, Ukraine should pursue a shrewd dual diplomacy. While advancing security and military cooperation with the government led by Prime Minister Tusk, it should maintain a separate channel with the presidential office to calmly discuss historical issues. Additionally, to avoid confrontation between politicians, encouraging dialogue through civilian historians and others would be effective. Next, the EU and the US should maximize their available leverage. The EU should use financial aid, and the US should use the security framework within NATO, as "leverage" to encourage Poland to act constructively. Crucially, the EU must not compromise on fundamental principles like the rule of law. Finally, all parties involved must not forget the fact that Russia is actively working behind the scenes in this conflict. The international community as a whole must stand firm against Russia's disinformation campaigns aimed at widening the rift between Poland and Ukraine. The common threat posed by Russia is the most compelling reason for us to unite now, far more so than immediate historical disputes or domestic political rivalries.

[#Pologne/#Ukraine] ⚡️🇵🇱✖️🇺🇦 La Pologne suspend le financement de Starlink pour l'Ukraine à partir du 1er octobre Le président polonais Karol Nawrocki a opposé son veto le 25 août au projet de loi prolongeant l'aide financière aux réfugiés ukrainiens, y compris le paiement de l'abonnement à Starlink. ⭕️ Sans cette loi, la Pologne n'aura pas de base juridique pour continuer les paiements, a déclaré Marek Georgika, représentant du ministère polonais des technologies numériques. Le ministre polonais des technologies numériques, Krzysztof Havkowski, a déclaré que cela pourrait compliquer la communication et la coordination des forces armées ukrainiennes, en particulier dans les zones proches du front. ⭕️ Auparavant, la Pologne avait fourni à l'Ukraine plus de 29 500 terminaux Starlink et couvrait leurs dépenses mensuelles, dont le montant total s'élevait à environ 323 millions de zlotys (environ 75 811 330 Euro) depuis 2022. Actuellement, l'Ukraine cherche des moyens alternatifs d'assurer la communication, ce qui semble être une tâche difficile.
